GSKbeta Assay: Types of GSK-3 assay used to test the selectivity/off target potential compounds of the invention with respect to PKC Î±/Î¸ inhibition activity includes the following: Type 1: The GSK-3 specific peptide used in this assay was derived from the phosphorylation site of glycogen synthase and its sequence is: YRRAAVPPSPSLSRHSSPHQ(S)EDEEE (SEQ ID NO: 1). The buffer used to make up the glycogen synthase peptide and [γ-33P] ATP consisted of MOPS 25 mM
